  "prompt": "Is morning sickness a sign of good pregnancy?",
  "response": "Morning sickness, which refers to nausea and vomiting that typically occurs in the early stages of pregnancy, is commonly experienced by many pregnant individuals. While it can be uncomfortable and distressing, some studies suggest that the presence of morning sickness may be associated with a lower risk of miscarriage and could indicate that the pregnancy is progressing normally.\n\nThat said, morning sickness varies widely among individuals. Some may experience it mildly, while others may have it more severely. It's important to note that not experiencing morning sickness does not necessarily mean that there is an issue with the pregnancy.\n\nUltimately, any concerns about morning sickness or pregnancy health should be discussed with a healthcare provider for personalized advice and support.",
